00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:39.840
group, okay? So let me remind you of a few&nbsp;
basic facts about 2x2 matrices. First of all,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:48.720
the matrix a b c d has determinant a d minus b c.&nbsp;
That's a number associated with a 2x2 matrix and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:56.000
here is the familiar product of two matrices and&nbsp;
here is the basic rule about determinants that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:01.120
if you take the determinant of a product of two&nbsp;
matrices, so A and B might be these two matrices,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:05.440
and then you take the determinant of this thing,&nbsp;
it turns out to be the product of the determinant&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:05.440 --> 00:03:12.800
of A times the determinant of B. So this is&nbsp;
the fundamental fact about determinants. In&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:12.800 --> 00:03:20.920
particular, if A and B both have determinant&nbsp;
