in form of an array a, okay, or a functional&nbsp;
set. By the way, the name for this group is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:05.960 --> 00:05:13.160
traditionally SL2 F2, the F2 referring to the&nbsp;
fact that we are basically working in a field&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:13.160 --> 00:05:20.520
with two elements. So for example, here are&nbsp;
two matrices—this one has determinant 1 - 0,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:27.440
that's one, this one has determinant 0 - 1, that's&nbsp;
minus one, but minus one is the same as 1 mod 2,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:27.440 --> 00:05:36.040
so this also is a matrix that belongs&nbsp;
to this set and the product is 1, 1,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:37.560 --> 00:05:49.640
1 + 1 is 2, which is the same as zero, and 1 +&nbsp;
0 is 1, and so that's also an entry of this set.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:49.640 --> 00:05:55.640
So we're using mod 2 arithmetic when we do the&nbsp;
multiplication. So note that this definition,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:55.640 --> 00:06:02.120
it's one of these A3 Prime definitions, it's&nbsp;
not very specific about what the set actually&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:02.120 --> 00:06:09.840
explicitly is and it does leave us to understand&nbsp;
what or to compute what the multiplication is. In&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:09.840 --> 00:06:14.880
other words, it's not telling us directly what&nbsp;
