00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:36.560
to be impossible because there's going to be an&nbsp;
unbounded number of such matrices. This is not a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:36.560 --> 00:12:46.680
finite group, it's unbounded, and in particular&nbsp;
these integers can get very big. So for example,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:47.360 --> 00:12:53.200
here is a matrix with determinant 1, 6 -&nbsp;
5, here's another one with determinant 1,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:53.200 --> 00:12:59.320
that's - 7 + 8, that's + one. So the product&nbsp;
of these two matrices is that one there,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:04.560
you can check, and you can also check that&nbsp;
